#compdef craco
# =============================================================================
# craco — Dilan Boskan / craco team's "Create React App
#         Configuration Override, an easy and comprehensible
#         configuration layer for Create React App" — a CLI that
#         WRAPS react-scripts (the build tool inside Create React
#         App) and INJECTS user-defined Webpack / Babel / Jest /
#         PostCSS / TypeScript / ESLint / DevServer config
#         overrides WITHOUT ejecting from CRA.  Distinguishing
#         from `react-app-rewired`, `customize-cra`, `react-
#         scripts-rewired`, and Vite migration paths by:
#           - DOGFOODS THE create-react-app WRAPPER PATTERN —
#             instead of forking react-scripts (CRA ejection),
#             craco preserves the CRA upgrade path by injecting
#             config at runtime before delegating to react-
#             scripts
#           - cosmiconfig-SEARCH-PLACES — craco.config.{ts,js,
#             cjs} / .cracorc.{ts,js} / .cracorc / "craco"
#             package.json key — all discovered automatically
#           - TYPESCRIPT-CONFIG SUPPORT via cosmiconfig-
#             typescript-loader: craco.config.ts is loaded +
#             compiled on the fly
#           - PLUGIN ARCHITECTURE: third-party @craco/plugin-*
#             packages can register Webpack/Babel/Jest tweaks
#             (e.g. @craco/plugin-less for LESS support,
#             craco-alias for path aliases, craco-antd for
#             Ant Design tree-shaking)
#           - 3 SUBCOMMANDS PASS-THROUGH: craco {build|start|
#             test} are direct replacements for react-scripts
#             {build|start|test} with config-override injected
#             before delegation
#           - --config FLAG: override the auto-discovered config
#             path (useful for monorepos with non-standard layout)
#           - --verbose FLAG: log every config-override
#             application + final merged config (useful for
#             debugging why an override didn't take effect)
#           - DEEP-MERGE OF OVERRIDES via deepMergeWithArray —
#             arrays in user config are merged element-wise with
#             react-scripts defaults
#           - JEST BINARY: `craco-jest` (second binary) wraps
#             `react-scripts test` with config overrides for
#             test runner integration
#         Used by: Create React App users who need to customize
#         Webpack / Babel / Jest / PostCSS WITHOUT ejecting,
#         monorepo maintainers integrating CRA apps into larger
#         workspaces, and design system teams that need to
#         tree-shake component libraries like Ant Design.
