# Library: cosmiconfig (https://github.com/cosmiconfig/cosmiconfig)
#          ("cosmiconfig" — David Clark (davidtheclark on GitHub) —
#           released 2015 as the dominant Node.js library for
#           CONFIG-FILE DISCOVERY across multiple standard
#           locations and formats.  Where Rust config-rs (R629)
#           and Go viper (R630) load configuration from
#           explicitly specified files, cosmiconfig SEARCHES for
#           the config file in a hierarchy of standard locations
#           by walking up from cwd to the filesystem root.
#           Distinct from every other Node config library by:
#             1. SEARCH-PLACES PATTERN — cosmiconfig's central
#                feature is the searchPlaces array, ordered by
#                priority:
#                  - package.json key (e.g. "eslintConfig" in
#                    package.json)
#                  - .{name}rc (no extension, JSON or YAML)
#                  - .{name}rc.json / .{name}rc.yaml / .{name}rc.yml
#                  - .{name}rc.js / .{name}rc.cjs / .{name}rc.mjs
#                  - .{name}rc.ts (with cosmiconfig-typescript-
#                    loader)
#                  - .config/{name}rc + .config/{name}rc.* (XDG)
#                  - {name}.config.js / .cjs / .mjs / .ts
#             2. UPWARD DIRECTORY WALKING — cosmiconfig walks
#                from cwd UP the directory tree to the
#                filesystem root, looking for the first config
#                file in any of the searchPlaces; this matches
#                how `git config` finds .git/config
#             3. PLUGGABLE LOADERS via the loaders option —
#                custom file extensions can be mapped to
#                arbitrary parser functions:
#                  cosmiconfig('myapp', {
#                      loaders: {
#                          '.toml': tomlLoader,
#                          '.ts': cosmiconfigTypescriptLoader(),
#                          noExt: (filepath, content) => ...,
#                      }
#                  })
#             4. SYNC AND ASYNC APIs — cosmiconfig() returns an
#                async explorer; cosmiconfigSync() returns a sync
#                explorer (for use cases like webpack plugins
#                that don't support async config loading)
#             5. PACKAGE.JSON KEY DISCOVERY — looking for a key
#                in package.json IS THE FIRST searchPlace by
#                default; this is the dominant Node convention
#                (eslintConfig, browserslist, prettier in
#                package.json all rely on cosmiconfig-style
#                discovery)
#             6. FOUNDATIONAL ADOPTION — cosmiconfig is the
#                discovery layer beneath ESLint, Prettier,
#                Stylelint, Browserslist, semantic-release,
#                lint-staged, Husky, commitlint, babel-plugin-
#                * config, and hundreds of other tools that
#                need "find my config file" semantics
#             7. CACHE — cosmiconfig caches search results by
#                default; subsequent search() calls return the
#                cached result unless clearCaches() is called)
